00:50:49,416 --> 00:51:10,191
Item B, what I am hoping to do in item B is provide an approach to the rest of the meeting so that we can be focused on those things that have support across the committee and that we can clearly outline for the public how we would like to hear from them tonight.

549
00:51:10,952 --> 00:51:17,557
So be it resolved that the Medford Comprehensive Heisman Building Committee will adopt the following procedure to manage the more than 200 space change proposals.

550
00:51:18,633 --> 00:51:23,297
One, public participation will occur before the committee begins deliberation.

551
00:51:24,337 --> 00:51:35,806
Number two, the public may speak in accordance with the rules adopted by the committee at our 5-13-2024 meeting, which is that the public will be limited to three minutes per individual and will be limited to those matters on the agenda.

552
00:51:36,206 --> 00:51:38,488
Speakers may only speak once on each topic.

553
00:51:39,743 --> 00:51:44,025
The chair shall limit the comments to two minutes based on the number of individuals wishing to speak.

554
00:51:44,585 --> 00:51:49,067
The chair will announce the time limit before the public comment period at every meeting.

555
00:51:49,508 --> 00:51:59,912
The public will also be encouraged to submit their comments in writing by emailing them to the SBC account, which is medfordmhsproject.medford.k12.nn.us.

556
00:52:00,613 --> 00:52:06,035
Emails received will be auto forwarded to members of the SBC, which has happened over the course of the last couple of days.

557
00:52:06,869 --> 00:52:11,592
Once public participation is closed, comments will only be taken by members or from the members of the committee.

558
00:52:12,312 --> 00:52:13,953
There are three categories of proposals.

559
00:52:14,093 --> 00:52:17,995
Each category will be reviewed and voted separately according to the below instructions.

560
00:52:18,975 --> 00:52:24,118
Category A, these are proposals by the educational leadership team put forward by Dr. Galluzzi.

561
00:52:24,698 --> 00:52:33,663
Proposals in this category do not impede the educational plan and are the result of typical expected dialogue between the project team and the educational leadership team at this phase in the process.

562
00:52:34,453 --> 00:52:42,735
Any member of the committee can make a resolution to approve one or multiple proposals by stating, motion to approve items X, Y, Z, whatever those numbers are.

563
00:52:43,976 --> 00:52:50,758
If a motion has a second, the committee will be permitted to ask clarifying questions and make statements, a roll call vote will then be called.

564
00:52:50,938 --> 00:52:57,680
For category B, these are proposals by other members of the committee that do not impede the educational plan as outlined by the project team.

565
00:52:59,772 --> 00:53:02,354
All members of the committee were invited to make proposals.

566
00:53:02,694 --> 00:53:09,519
Motions for approval and a second must be made by a voting member who did not submit the proposal or proposals.

567
00:53:10,200 --> 00:53:20,628
Resolution to approve one or multiple proposals can be made by stating, motion to approve items X, Y, and Z. If a motion has a second, the committee will be permitted to ask clarifying questions and make statements.

568
00:53:20,868 --> 00:53:23,090
A roll call vote will be called.

569
00:53:24,070 --> 00:53:24,551
Category C.

570
00:53:25,241 --> 00:53:32,026
proposals by other members of the committee that would impede the educational plan as defined by the project team.

571
00:53:33,428 --> 00:53:36,090
All members of the committee who were invited to make proposals.

572
00:53:36,150 --> 00:53:44,557
However, the member comprehensive high school building committee does not have the authority to change the educational plan or put forward a building design that does not support the educational plan.

573
00:53:45,117 --> 00:53:52,543
Instead, members of the committee may request that an item be referred to the school committee for review and consideration as the next round of educational plan updates are made.

574
00:53:53,054 --> 00:53:58,759
Motions for approval in a second must be made by a voting member who did not submit the proposals or proposal.

575
00:53:59,399 --> 00:54:07,025
A resolution to approve one or multiple proposals can be made by stating motion to refer items X, Y, Z to the school committee for consideration.

576
00:54:07,646 --> 00:54:12,510
If a motion has a second, the committee will be permitted to ask clarifying questions and make statements.

577
00:54:12,930 --> 00:54:14,451
A roll call vote will then be called.

578
00:54:15,432 --> 00:54:20,236
As a reminder, the member comprehensive high school building committee adopted the below rules at our 513 meeting.

579
00:54:22,349 --> 00:54:25,911
Members may speak twice on any debatable motion for up to three minutes.

580
00:54:26,252 --> 00:54:30,194
Once voting begins, no voting member may speak other than to indicate how they are voting.

581
00:54:31,015 --> 00:54:44,544
So again, the goal is for us to move through more than 200 space change proposals this evening, first by hearing from the public, then we'll close public comment, and then we will take each category one at a time.

582
00:54:45,425 --> 00:54:49,768
And under this proposal, we also

583
00:54:50,338 --> 00:55:04,662
would be asking for somebody other than the submitter to make the proposal for consideration, which for me, as I put this forward, just signaled that there is support for the idea by more than just the individual who submitted.

584
00:55:05,483 --> 00:55:07,103
And there's 200 options.

585
00:55:07,143 --> 00:55:10,324
So I think we have to have a way to sort of prioritize.

586
00:55:11,665 --> 00:55:12,405
Any questions?

587
00:55:15,526 --> 00:55:15,746
Luke?

588
00:55:15,866 --> 00:55:17,046
Not a question.

589
00:55:17,106 --> 00:55:18,447
I'd just like to make a statement.

590
00:55:19,387 --> 00:55:19,587
Sure.

591
00:55:20,537 --> 00:55:22,038
So- Is it about this motion?

592
00:55:22,378 --> 00:55:23,179
It's about this motion.

593
00:55:23,199 --> 00:55:23,459
Great.

594
00:55:24,579 --> 00:55:37,207
So to members of the committee, members of the community, I want to speak now before we kind of take these up to offer context that many may not know.

595
00:55:39,368 --> 00:55:42,850
So I'm here because I want to see a new high school built in Medford.

596
00:55:44,331 --> 00:55:50,074
I was a co-author of the statement of interest that brought us into the MSBA program

597
00:55:51,834 --> 00:55:53,075
Again that worked in 2021.

598
00:55:53,135 --> 00:55:55,896
We've reviewed prior attempts.

599
00:55:56,256 --> 00:55:57,377
We understood why they failed.

600
00:55:58,357 --> 00:56:02,540
Ultimately measure prevailed and we were admitted to the core program in 2023.

601
00:56:03,940 --> 00:56:05,741
This SPC has been working since then.

602
00:56:06,402 --> 00:56:09,203
I'm speaking as a parent of three children.

603
00:56:09,583 --> 00:56:16,047
I have one in primary school one at the middle and my oldest attends this high school.

604
00:56:16,727 --> 00:56:18,688
I want them and all of our students

605
00:56:19,527 --> 00:56:23,148
to benefit from a new high school that truly meets their needs.

606
00:56:23,628 --> 00:56:24,429
This one doesn't.

607
00:56:26,889 --> 00:56:33,191
Our primary and middle schools are relatively comfortable and effective facilities.

608
00:56:34,331 --> 00:56:35,712
The high school doesn't meet that standard.

609
00:56:37,192 --> 00:56:42,474
Today, tonight, we'll probably hear some strong views and some real disagreement.

610
00:56:43,374 --> 00:56:46,215
I think that's normal and healthy in a democratic community.

611
00:56:47,466 --> 00:56:55,709
I actually come from a formerly communist nation, and so I cherish the ability to honestly discuss things.

612
00:56:58,570 --> 00:57:07,974
So my hope is that we can express these views firmly but respectfully, avoid some of the rhetoric and revision that we see at the national level.

613
00:57:09,434 --> 00:57:16,517
We share a common goal, I think, and that's doing what's best for our students or city, even if we differ on how to get there.

614
00:57:18,636 --> 00:57:28,181
Our new school committee developed an educational plan that, in my opinion, departs from a nominal combined high school locational model.

615
00:57:28,221 --> 00:57:42,390
It combines school functions with broader community services, which is great, but that vision also arrives with a very large facility and a very large price tag.

616
00:57:43,130 --> 00:57:46,953
And we're now looking at a proposal that's

617
00:57:47,454 --> 00:57:51,895
approaching a billion dollars, which is unusual by, I'll say, American standards.

618
00:57:53,856 --> 00:58:00,558
So I think it's reasonable and appropriate for the community to scrutinize a project of this scale and cost.

619
00:58:02,099 --> 00:58:11,782
My feedback and motions on the space plan have been presented on the agenda in a way that may sound negative, but I think I would frame it differently.

620
00:58:13,142 --> 00:58:15,243
I think because of this process, many more people

621
00:58:15,995 --> 00:58:22,437
have now read the detailed space summary with its hundreds of proposed spaces, 415.

622
00:58:25,517 --> 00:58:28,618
So I think the public awareness is a positive outcome.

623
00:58:30,659 --> 00:58:44,422
And just, you know, over the past couple of weeks, we were asked to review proposed spaces and encouraged or guided to enter those responses in a digital format.

624
00:58:45,386 --> 00:58:53,548
So I approached that task with the same precision and diligence that I approached the SOI task.

625
00:58:54,768 --> 00:59:01,109
And so you'll see the cross-referencing of guidelines and the selected SOI priorities.

626
00:59:01,129 --> 00:59:04,170
We picked five and seven in my inputs.

627
00:59:05,370 --> 00:59:13,872
And frankly, where I felt that the spaces didn't align with one or the other, I recommended deletion or reduction to spur discussion.

628
00:59:15,563 --> 00:59:25,090
You know, I would like to align this project with the commitments that brought us to the program, but I'm not trying to undermine the school.

629
00:59:26,471 --> 00:59:27,192
I want a school.

630
00:59:28,973 --> 00:59:40,042
But I also want to maximize reimbursement and not unduly burden vulnerable residents in our community on fixed incomes.

631
00:59:41,623 --> 00:59:43,584
And, you know,

632
00:59:44,881 --> 00:59:47,683
I don't necessarily expect many of my motions to pass.

633
00:59:47,803 --> 00:59:52,906
I'm familiar with my track record, but I think it's good to talk about things.

634
00:59:53,707 --> 00:59:56,029
