But by my calculations, if you're talking about a high school of 640,000 square feet, and you calculate what the MSBA will reimburse, again, the numbers aren't firm, but you're talking about a $625 million debt exclusion.

752
01:08:59,905 --> 01:09:05,907
And that's about two grand per average single family home.

753
01:09:06,826 --> 01:09:10,568
Mayor, can we have this conversation when we can have a full conversation?

754
01:09:10,628 --> 01:09:16,651
Like, I don't think this serves anybody to sort of drop high level numbers on the table.

755
01:09:16,951 --> 01:09:23,394
And like, I understand the concern and I think it warrants a dedicated conversation with a lot of information.

756
01:09:23,414 --> 01:09:27,517
I don't think that's what we're going to achieve tonight.

757
01:09:27,537 --> 01:09:33,600
If we- I think it has to be discussed a little bit because tonight we have, we're a committee

758
01:09:34,989 --> 01:09:39,510
wants to see the biggest and the best for our kids and our faculty.

759
01:09:39,870 --> 01:10:02,277
I'm one of those people, but it needs to be mentioned because I also put in space reductions, not because I don't want the biggest and the best high school, but I want to reduce space and in the end, reduce costs for all of our residents who live here and rent here, because the amount of this project is,

760
01:10:03,587 --> 01:10:05,469
is quite honestly scary to me.

761
01:10:05,489 --> 01:10:12,874
Number one, for it not to pass after we've done so much work, especially you Chair Graham.

762
01:10:13,495 --> 01:10:23,683
And number two, if it does pass and it's just slightly passed, you're gonna have a lot of people that are gonna really struggle to pay for these tax increases.

763
01:10:24,183 --> 01:10:31,529
So I'll just say it bluntly, we really do not have debt capacity to put much of this on the city's debt.

764
01:10:32,068 --> 01:10:48,079
We have capital needs from a new fire station, to roads and streets and sidewalks, to a rec center that is flooded, you know, was just flooded, to the Hegner Center, to needing to rehab Hormel Stadium, and the list goes on and on.

765
01:10:48,179 --> 01:10:57,346
So I will wait for the full-blown presentation in May, which I think is fine, because I know we can continue to reduce space.

766
01:10:58,035 --> 01:11:00,837
but I think people need to hear it before they vote.

767
01:11:00,877 --> 01:11:06,300
We have a 15 member body that doesn't wanna vote to eliminate space.

768
01:11:06,480 --> 01:11:09,682
I don't wanna vote to eliminate space, but it has to be heard.

769
01:11:09,702 --> 01:11:22,269
I mean, there has to be some level of just transparency of where we're at and how much is this gonna cost the average taxpayer or the average renter before we even take these votes tonight.

770
01:11:22,409 --> 01:11:25,011
So no, I'm not gonna give you the full presentation.

771
01:11:25,828 --> 01:11:35,671
was hoping to tonight that will wait till 527, but we do have some numbers and it's time to be open about that and honest because it's going to help this committee.

772
01:11:36,131 --> 01:11:37,292
It's not to scare anybody.

773
01:11:37,412 --> 01:11:39,252
This is just the facts.

774
01:11:39,953 --> 01:11:47,235
It's going to help this committee maybe vote to reduce some space now and in the future.

775
01:11:48,139 --> 01:12:02,832
knowing that we all want the same thing in the end, a new high school that meets the needs of all of our students and our faculty, but that isn't 640,000 square feet and isn't the most expensive in the nation.

776
01:12:02,852 --> 01:12:05,755
Emily?

777
