785
01:13:04,345 --> 01:13:06,607
The numbers aren't on all designs.

786
01:13:07,047 --> 01:13:07,748
It ranges from

787
01:13:08,364 --> 01:13:16,171
like 815 million to 900 million, and one can go and figure out what the MSBA will possibly reimburse.

788
01:13:17,012 --> 01:13:18,633
And it's about 625 million.

789
01:13:19,714 --> 01:13:20,495
I've figured it out.

790
01:13:20,695 --> 01:13:25,379
There's people on this committee that I'm sure have also figured it out, and there's residents who have figured it out.

791
01:13:25,820 --> 01:13:30,184
So it's like, I don't know how we can't be at least mentioning it.

792
01:13:31,095 --> 01:13:32,976
And it's not creating fear.

793
01:13:34,017 --> 01:13:34,738
They're facts.

794
01:13:35,178 --> 01:13:36,339
It's the reality we're in.

795
01:13:36,979 --> 01:13:43,524
And I just think I have the right to explain it to this committee and talk about it.

796
01:13:43,904 --> 01:13:54,152
We have a vote to take in 13 months that we need to pass for our students, but we also need to put the facts on the table for the residents.

797
01:13:54,372 --> 01:13:58,195
And this committee, I think, needs to reduce the space

798
01:13:58,998 --> 01:14:09,302
and in the end reduce the cost, still creating a wonderful project for our community at large, especially our kids, but it does need to be discussed.

799
01:14:11,223 --> 01:14:11,443
Jen?

800
01:14:12,283 --> 01:14:17,886
Yes, I just wanted to make it clear about the MSBA numbers and reimbursement and what we know at this stage.

801
01:14:18,526 --> 01:14:23,268
We do not have MSBA feedback from the PDP level report that's been submitted.

802
01:14:23,308 --> 01:14:26,029
We do not know what their comments are.

803
01:14:26,049 --> 01:14:28,310
We do, we've been in touch with them, we expect those,

804
01:14:28,892 --> 01:14:29,813
in the next week or so.

805
01:14:30,813 --> 01:14:42,602
But without that information, we really can't do any kind of accurate even guessing at the potential reimbursement rate and the effective rate as discussed in our last meeting.

806
01:14:42,622 --> 01:14:47,105
So I just want to be really clear that the MSBA has not provided any feedback yet.

807
01:14:47,446 --> 01:14:56,993
And there's a way to do your calculations on what's on the MSBA website and things, but that's not necessarily

808
01:14:57,957 --> 01:15:01,058
Medford High School specific information.

809
01:15:01,118 --> 01:15:03,178
So I just want to make sure that that's pretty clear.

810
01:15:03,198 --> 01:15:17,262
And that is what we're expecting to be able to do and have more in-depth input from them, be able to take a deeper dive into the spaces of how that relates to reimbursement costs by the meeting on May 27th.

811
01:15:17,302 --> 01:15:26,565
